history.content: Unfortunately, the two options you've described are not actually options because our 186 instructor probably will not be involved with enrollment (our faculty usually are not involved), and it is unlikely that a calcentral system admin will manually enroll students as the waitlists are now automatically processed. So really, your options are to wait for students from your section to drop or switch sections. Sadly, in order to switch sections, you will need to drop the course entirely and re-add. Despite doing this, you might still increase your chances since your current section selection is full. What section are you currently waitlisted for?

children.subject: since there are other sections that have more seats than the # of students on the waitlist, and your section is completely full, it's probably better for you to drop and re-add.
I'm currently waitlisted for  section 105 Monday 3-4 Dwinelle

Since there are open seats in your section and your WL positions is < than the # of available seats, sounds like staying there should be just fine. I don't have any guesses on your chances as it depends on how many students ahead of you are also CS/EECS Majors since there are only 157 seats left. For example, if all 239 students ahead of you were eecs/cs majors, your chances are probably unlikely unfortunately. However, if there are lots of non-majors ahead of you, you would have priority over non-majors.

I'm also on the 186 waitlist.  I'm waitlisted for a section with 25 open seats and I'm 14th on the waitlist (presumably, since I just moved section and there are 14 people on the waitlist.

However, I'm 239th on the waitlist and there are 157 open seats in the lecture.  Is there a good chance I'm getting in or should I be switching my units to something I have a better chance in?  I need one last EECS class to graduate, if I don't get into this class or something else worth 4 EECS units I won't be able to graduate.

history.content: Hi there, I'm a 3rd year declared CS major currently waitlisted for CS 186. Luckily the class hasn't seemed to finished enrollment and my current waitlist position should be enough to get into the class. I phase 2ed the class and I added myself to, at the time of my phase 2, an available section, but unfortunately was waitlisted due to what looked like the 70% enrollment rule. The problem is now I'm still on the waitlist and it seems the section I enrolled in has filled up completely. I seen the posts where it seems you can't be added into the class if you are waitlisted for section, and you can't swap sections if you are on the waitlist. However, at the same time, I fear that there won't be enough spots if I end up on the end of the waitlist. Is it possible I can email the CS 186 instructor or Calcentral system admin to manually add me in before I get skipped over? Or are these my two options, and if so which would end up having a higher chance of getting me into the class. Thank you!
history.subject: Advice on drop/readd myself to new section or wait it out and hope Instructor adds me CS 186?
